HEADWORD: Fanion
<hw>Fan"ion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Fanon</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A small flag
sometimes carried at the head of the baggage of a brigade.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A small flag for marking the stations in
surveying.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fanlike</ent>⟦br⟧
